11/01/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Ivaylo Kalfin said on Wednesday (January 10th) that as an EU member, Bulgaria expects the Union to exert "strong pressure on Libya and demonstrate strong engagement" in support of five Bulgarian nurses, sentenced to death in Libya in a controversial HIV case.
Kalfin added that he expects the issue to be one of the main topics of discussion during the January 22nd meeting of the EU General Affairs Council.
Also Wednesday, Bulgaria confirmed that Libya has finally approved a visit by Deputy Justice Minister Margarit Ganev.
She plans to meet with the nurses in prison to discuss possible changes in their defence team.
(Sega - 11/01/07;
BNR, bTV - 10/01/07)
